Configure The Git
git config --global user.name "username"       --config username
git config --global user.email "email"         --config username
git config --list                              --Display the config ie username and email


Git Status And Git Clone
git clone url                                  --copy repo in local machine
git status                                     --return the status



There are three types of Status:
untracked                                     --new file and we havent add and commit
unstaged                                      --we have add but didnt commit
unchanged                                     --nothing to do
changed                                       --we havent add and commit


Git Add and commit
git add filename                             --to add specific file
git add .                                    --to add all file that is changed and untracked
git commit -m "commit"                       --to add commit


upload local repo content to remote repo
git push [alias] [branch]                      --to add my this repo to alias in branch [branch]
git remote add aliasName url                   --to create alis 
git push -u [alias] [branch]                   --save the alis and branch for next time so that we can push localrepo by git push for next time


Git INitilization
git init                                      --to INitilize the git



Git Branches
git branch                                     --to list the git branch
git branch -m oldbranch newbranch              --to rename branch
git checkout branchname                         --to switch branch
git checkout -b branchname                     --to create branch
git branch -d branchname                       --to delete branch
                                               --remember while deleting branch you should be in another branch
git diff branchname                            --to compare current branch with branchname


Git merge
git merge branchname                          --this merge current branch with branchname
Pull Req using Git                            --By making pull request using git


git pull
git pull [alis] [branch]                     --update remote change in local repo



Undoing Changes
If You have add Only
git reset filename                           --reset the add changes that hasnt commit of file filename
git reset                                    --reset the add changes that hasnt commit of all file

If we comit too
git reset HEAD~1                             --reset the repo one stage back 
git reset [comit hash]                       --reset the repo to the comithash
git reset --hard [comithash]                 --reset the repo to the comit hass reflect edit in our editor too
git log                                       --to see all the hashes and log



git fork
wile contributing to opensource we do fork and its like our own repo and perform all actifity and at last we make pull req using github
